=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Mono-Boc protect 1,4-diaminobutane to BocNH(CH2)4NH2 | Step 2: Sulfonylate the मुक्त amine with 2,4-dichlorobenzenesulfonyl chloride, then de-Boc to give H2N(CH2)4NHSO2(2,4-dichlorophenyl) | Step 3: Do enantiopure epoxide opening with (R)-methyl glycidyl ether (or via (R)-epichlorohydrin → glycidyl ether) to form the chiral amino alcohol HOCH2CH(OMe)CH2NH(CH2)4NHSO2Ar | Step 4: Reprotect that amine as Boc to give the orthogonally protected amino alcohol | Step 5: O-carbamylate the alcohol with phenyl isocyanate to install the O-phenyl carbamate | Step 6: Remove Boc and trap the free amine with iPrNCO to form the terminal isopropyl urea, furnishing COC[C@@H](CN(CCCCNS(=O)(=O)c1ccc(Cl)cc1Cl)C(=O)NC(C)C)OC(=O)Nc1ccccc1

